<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,1556,2013]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
TYPE. 
<collectionCode box="[224,269,1591,1616]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">ZSI</collectionCode>
, collection number unknown (
<bibRefCitation author="Annandale, N." box="[609,799,1591,1616]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="81 - 93" refId="ref45508" refString="Annandale, N. (1905) Notes on the Oriental lizards in the Indian Museum, with a list of species recorded from British India and Ceylon. Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal, 2, 81 - 93." type="journal article" year="1905">Annandale 1905</bibRefCitation>
); 
<typeStatus box="[819,923,1591,1616]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Holotype</typeStatus>
<collectionCode box="[930,1011,1591,1616]" country="Denmark" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/mci8-ehqk" name="Zoological Museum, University of Copenhagen" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">ZMUC</collectionCode>
3476 (Field No. 143) (
<taxonomicName box="[1271,1419,1592,1616]" class="Reptilia" family="Sphaerodactylidae" genus="Pristurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="iranicus">
<emphasis box="[1271,1419,1592,1616]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">P. r. iranicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). TYPE LOCALITY. Originally “insulae Kharg vel Karrack in sinu Persico, .. a 
<collectingRegion box="[1023,1105,1628,1653]" country="Oman" name="Masqat" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Maskat</collectingRegion>
in littore Arabico” [= Kharg Island, Persian Gulf and 
<collectingCountry box="[429,514,1664,1687]" name="Oman" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Muscat</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[525,600,1663,1688]" name="Oman" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Oman</collectingCountry>
]; restricted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schmidt, K. P." box="[764,939,1663,1688]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 2" refId="ref64743" refString="Schmidt, K. P. (1952) Diagnoses of new Amphibians and Reptiles from Iran. Natural History Miscellanea, Chicago Academy of Sciences, 93, 1 - 2." type="journal article" year="1952">Schmidt (1952)</bibRefCitation>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[974,1060,1664,1687]" name="Oman" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Muscat</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,1556,2013]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
DISTRIBUTION. Along the Arabian coast from 
<collectingCountry box="[699,774,1700,1725]" name="Jordan" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Jordan</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[820,902,1700,1725]" name="Kuwait" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Kuwait</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[967,1015,1700,1723]" name="Iran" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Iran</collectingCountry>
, present also in coastal 
<collectingCountry box="[1307,1383,1700,1725]" name="Eritrea" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Eritrea</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,247,1735,1760]" name="Somalia" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Somalia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,1556,2013]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3342274535" country="Iran" location="Baluchistan Prov." municipality="Gulf of Oman" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Bushehr">
DISTRIBUTION IN 
<collectingCountry box="[353,409,1772,1795]" name="Iran" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">IRAN</collectingCountry>
. 
<figureCitation box="[425,523,1772,1797]" captionStart="FIGURES 140–145. 140" captionStartId="95.[151,264,1557,1580]" captionTargetBox="[171,1416,213,1516]" captionTargetId="figure-54@95.[151,1436,193,1536]" captionTargetPageId="95" captionText="FIGURES 140–145. 140. Trachylepis septemtaeniata. 141. Trachylepis vittata. 142. Pristurus rupestris. Blue square denotes the type locality for P. r. iranicus. 143. Teratoscincus bedriagai. 144. Teratoscincus keyserlingii. 145. Teratoscincus microlepis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4929781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4929781/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 142</figureCitation>
. Restricted to coastal areas along the Persian Gulf and 
<collectingMunicipality box="[1157,1318,1772,1797]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Gulf of Oman</collectingMunicipality>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1334,1432,1772,1797]" country="Iran" name="Bushehr" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Bushehr</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[151,202,1808,1831]" country="Iran" name="Fars" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fars</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[216,351,1808,1832]" country="Iran" name="Hormozgan" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Hormozgan</collectingRegion>
, and Sistan and 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C387F2FFA3FF89FF5B493652BCFC94:8EB5603FFFA3FF96FDD3482D5495F884" box="[543,749,1807,1832]" country="Iran" municipality="Gulf of Oman" name="Baluchistan Prov." pageId="47" pageNumber="48" stateProvince="Bushehr">Baluchistan Prov.</location>
). The most inland record is only about 
<quantity box="[1209,1283,1807,1832]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" unit="km" value="35.0">35 km</quantity>
from the sea shore
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,1556,2013]" box="[151,1387,1879,1904]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">HABITAT. A typical climber found on rocks, large boulders, tree trunks, but also houses, stone walls and ruins.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="48" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,1556,2013]" lastBlockId="48.[151,1440,151,824]" lastPageId="48" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
REMARKS. The subspecies 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmidt" authorityName="Schmidt" box="[458,703,1916,1941]" class="Reptilia" family="Sphaerodactylidae" genus="Pristurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="iranicus">
<emphasis box="[458,602,1917,1940]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">P. r. iranicus</emphasis>
Schmidt
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[720,770,1916,1941]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">type</typeStatus>
locality 
<collectingRegion box="[870,965,1916,1941]" country="Iran" name="Bushehr" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Bushehr</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[978,1141,1916,1941]" country="Iran" name="Bushehr" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Bushehr Prov.</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1153,1202,1916,1941]" name="Iran" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Iran</collectingCountry>
), whose diagnosis is based mostly on differences in coloration, is not widely accepted (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Anderson, S. C." box="[979,1157,1952,1977]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" refId="ref45318" refString="Anderson, S. C. (1999) The lizards of Iran. Society for the Study of Amphibians and Reptiles, Oxford, Ohio, 442 pp." type="book" year="1999">Anderson 1999</bibRefCitation>
, p. 177). 
<bibRefCitation author="Badiane, A. &amp; Garcia-Porta, J. &amp; Cervenka, J. &amp; Kratochvil, L. &amp; Sindaco, R. &amp; Robinson, M. D. &amp; Morales, H. &amp; Mazuch, T. &amp; Price, T. &amp; Amat, F. &amp; Shobrak, M. Y. &amp; Wilms, T. &amp; Simo-Riudalbas, M. &amp; Ahmadzadeh, F. &amp; Papenfuss, T. J. &amp; Cluchier, A. &amp; Viglione, J. &amp; Carranza, S." pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="33 - 58" refId="ref46307" refString="Badiane, A., Garcia-Porta, J., Cervenka, J., Kratochvil, L., Sindaco, R., Robinson, M. D., Morales, H., Mazuch, T., Price, T., Amat, F. Shobrak, M. Y., Wilms, T., Simo-Riudalbas, M., Ahmadzadeh, F., Papenfuss, T. J., Cluchier, A., Viglione, J. &amp; Carranza, S. (2014) Phylogenetic relationships of Semaphore geckos (Squamata: Sphaerodactylidae: Pristurus) with an assessment of the taxonomy of Pristurus rupestris. Zootaxa, 3885 (1), 33 - 58. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3835.1.2" type="journal article" year="2014">
Badiane 
<emphasis box="[1376,1436,1952,1977]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
recovered 
<taxonomicName box="[352,496,1989,2012]" class="Reptilia" family="Sphaerodactylidae" genus="Pristurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="iranicus">
<emphasis box="[352,496,1989,2012]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">P. r. iranicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nested within 
<taxonomicName box="[664,816,1989,2012]" class="Reptilia" family="Sphaerodactylidae" genus="Pristurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="rupestris">
<emphasis box="[664,816,1989,2012]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">P. r. rupestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
implying that the former is a younger synonym of the nominotypical form. However, the authors did not have material from the 
<typeStatus box="[1002,1050,152,176]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Torki, Ahmadzadeh, Ilgaz, Avci &amp; Kumlutas" authorityYear="2011" box="[1185,1277,152,175]" class="Reptilia" family="Phyllodactylidae" genus="Asaccus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="iranicus">
<emphasis box="[1185,1277,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">iranicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
available and they refrained from making any taxonomic decisions. Based on phylogenetic analyses of morphological and osteological characters 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blanford" authorityYear="1874" box="[433,570,224,248]" class="Reptilia" family="Sphaerodactylidae" genus="Pristurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rupestris">
<emphasis box="[433,570,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">P. rupestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to morphologically more advanced forms grouped in ‘the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ruppell" authorityYear="1835" class="Reptilia" family="Sphaerodactylidae" genus="Pristurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavipunctatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">P. flavipunctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
assemblage’ (
<bibRefCitation author="Arnold, E. N." box="[469,618,260,285]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref45905" refString="Arnold, E. N. (2009) Relationships, evolution and biogeography of Semaphore geckos, Pristurus (Squamata, Sphaerodactylidae) based on morphology. Zootaxa, 2060, 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="2009">Arnold 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
