<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1440,151,824]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
HABITAT. Loose windblown sands with shrubby vegetation. (Zarudny 
<emphasis box="[958,990,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">ex.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Szczerbak, N. N. &amp; Golubev, M. L." box="[999,1317,692,717]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refId="ref66267" refString="Szczerbak, N. N. &amp; Golubev, M. L. (1996) Gecko fauna of the USSR and contiguous regions. Society for the Study of Amphibians and Reptiles, Oxfor, Ohio, 233 pp." type="book" year="1996">Szczerbak &amp; Golubev 1996</bibRefCitation>
) observed this species on gravel soil with a thin layer of salt crust. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hojati, V. &amp; Kami, H. G. &amp; Faghiri, A. &amp; Ahmadzadeh, F." box="[785,1001,727,752]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="113 - 115" refId="ref53458" refString="Hojati, V., Kami, H. G., Faghiri, A. &amp; Ahmadzadeh, F. (2009) A morphological study of the Bedriaga plate-tailed gecko, Teratoscincus bedriagai Nikolsky, 1900, in Semnan province of Iran (Reptilia: Gekkonidae). Zoology in the Middle East, 46, 113 - 115. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 09397140.2009.10638337" type="journal article" year="2009">
Hojati 
<emphasis box="[862,919,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">et al.</emphasis>
(2009)
</bibRefCitation>
reports it from clayey and loamy soils near 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Anderson" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[206,301,765,788]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tamaricaceae" genus="Tamarix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[206,301,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Tamarix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bushes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
